" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 16, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xbe1665702773834.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xbe1665702773834.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xbe1665702773834.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xbe1665702773834\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">View the ProcScript call stack to see the modules that are called or activated at\n      runtime, or to identify where to put a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try-catch</span> block to handle\n      exceptions.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__p_d175655e1_d175656e1_d175657e1\">When script modules are called or activated at runtime, the call is added to the ProcScript call stack, along with their associated component names and line numbers. The most recent module appears at the top of the call stack.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__p_d175658e1_d175659e1_d175660e1\">When a module is called recursively, a level of ProcScript nesting is added to the call stack. If the nesting level reaches 500, Uniface issues a fatal error message (<code class=\"ph codeph\">9033 \"Runtime error: Proc stack overflow\"</code>).</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__section_ecz_mr3_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d218195e66\">Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__p_d175664e1_d175665e1_d175666e1\">The following fields are displayed in the\n            debugger:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__ul_nxg_nr3_1xb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__li_d53525e1_d53526e1_d53527e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Component</span>—the name of the component in which the calling\n               ProcScript module is located. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__li_d53528e1_d53529e1_d53530e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Module</span>—the name of the ProcScript module that has activated or\n               called another module. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__li_d53531e1_d53532e1_d53533e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Line</span>—the line number of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> or\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">call</span> command for the module that has called or activated\n               another module. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__li_d53534e1_d53535e1_d53536e1\"> Code—the ProcScript code that performs the\n               activation or call. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__section_h3f_pr3_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d218195e105\">Viewing the call stack</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__p_d175670e1_d175671e1_d175672e1\">To view the call stack, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Call Stack</span></span> from the debugger menu.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__p_d175673e1_d175674e1_d175675e1\">To view a ProcScript module listed in the call\n            stack, double-click it to open it in the Browser, or choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Show in\n               Browser</span> from the context menu.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xbe1665702773834__note_nfn_pr3_1xb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> It only possible to open components and Global\n            ProcScripts, not application shells.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bdc1665702761852.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ProcScript Call Stack</a><p>When script modules are called or activated at runtime, the call is added to the ProcScript call stack, along with their associated component names and line numbers. The most recent module appears at the top of the call stack.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxo1665702773911.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Monitoring ProcScript Modules</a><p>The Uniface Debugger allows you to monitor and control the execution of ProcScript.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nys1665703528633.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Debugger Browser</a><p>Use the Debugger Browser to view the structure and ProcScript modules of components and Global ProcScript library. You can also toggle breakpoints in a ProcScript module, watch fields and variables, or change their values.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533624\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533624\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Call Stack Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 View the ProcScript call stack to see the modules that are called or activated at runtime, or to identify where to put a try-catch block to handle exceptions. When script modules are called or activated at runtime, the call is added to the ProcScript call stack, along with their associated component names and line numbers. The most recent module appears at the top of the call stack. When a module is called recursively, a level of ProcScript nesting is added to the call stack. If the nesting level reaches 500, Uniface issues a fatal error message ( 9033 \"Runtime error: Proc stack overflow\" ). Fields The following fields are displayed in the debugger: Component —the name of the component in which the calling ProcScript module is located. Module —the name of the ProcScript module that has activated or called another module. Line —the line number of the activate or call command for the module that has called or activated another module. Code—the ProcScript code that performs the activation or call. Viewing the call stack To view the call stack, choose View > Call Stack from the debugger menu. To view a ProcScript module listed in the call stack, double-click it to open it in the Browser, or choose Show in Browser from the context menu. Note: It only possible to open components and Global ProcScripts, not application shells. Related Links ProcScript Call Stack When script modules are called or activated at runtime, the call is added to the ProcScript call stack, along with their associated component names and line numbers. The most recent module appears at the top of the call stack. Monitoring ProcScript Modules The Uniface Debugger allows you to monitor and control the execution of ProcScript. Debugger Browser Use the Debugger Browser to view the structure and ProcScript modules of components and Global ProcScript library. You can also toggle breakpoints in a ProcScript module, watch fields and variables, or change their values. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}